        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): regenerate native hook descriptors when relay unavailable after restart",
        "body": "## Problem\nNative hook direct-bridge errors hard-deny when relay is unavailable after gateway restart. Stale native hook descriptors are not regenerated, and Codex app-server relay invocation failures do not fall back to generic OpenClaw before-tool-call policy.\n\nFixes #89325\n\n## Fix\nChange stale native hook direct-bridge errors to fall through to gateway RPC instead of hard-denying. Change Codex app-server relay invocation failures to fall back to generic OpenClaw before-tool-call policy evaluation.\n\n## Test plan\n1. Verify native hook relay CLI handles regeneration on unavailable relay\n2. Verify Codex app-server approval bridge tests pass\n3. Verify before_tool_call policy, trusted policies, loop detection, and approval prompts still enforce after fallback\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Before (broken)\n- Native hook direct-bridge encounters stale descriptor → hard-deny error\n- Gateway restart invalidates native hook relay connection → hooks stop working entirely\n- Codex app-server relay invocation failure → no fallback, tool call rejected without policy evaluation\n- Requires manual gateway restart or hook descriptor regeneration to recover\n\n### After (fixed)\n- Stale native hook descriptor error → falls through to gateway RPC instead of hard-denying\n- Relay unavailable after gateway restart → hooks regenerate via gateway RPC fallback\n- Codex app-server relay invocation failure → falls back to generic OpenClaw before-tool-call policy\n- Automatic recovery without manual intervention\n\n### Reproduction\n1. Start gateway with native hooks configured\n2. Restart gateway (relay connection becomes stale)\n3. Before fix: native hook calls fail with hard-deny errors\n4. After fix: hooks fall through to gateway RPC and regenerate automatically\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.test.ts (20 tests, 100% pass)\n✓ extensions/codex/src/app-server/approval-bridge.test.ts (64 tests, 100% pass)\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  84 passed (84)\n   Duration  41.0s\n```\n\nAll 84 tests pass across CLI native hook relay and Codex approval bridge. Tests cover relay regeneration, fallback paths, and policy enforcement after fallback.",
